        <div class=3D"post-body">
            <span id=3D"hs_cos_wrapper_post_body" class=3D"hs_cos_wrapper h=
s_cos_wrapper_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text" style=3D"" data-hs-=
cos-general-type=3D"meta_field" data-hs-cos-type=3D"rich_text"><p><span sty=
le=3D"color: black; background-color: white;">An accurate, scientific incid=
ent investigation relies on evidence. Evidence is collected to validate cau=
se-and-effect relationships and better understand what happened and why. Do=
cumenting, organizing and keeping track of evidence can be just as importan=
t as collecting the evidence. In the <em>Cause Mapping</em> Investigation T=
emplate in Microsoft Excel, the problem definition, analysis, documentation=
 and evidence are all stored within one file for easier access and quick re=
ference. </span><span style=3D"color: black;">In this blog, we=E2=80=99re f=
ocusing on one worksheet in particular: the Notes worksheet.</span></p>
<!--more-->
<p><span style=3D"color: black; background-color: white;">The 19-worksheet =
</span><a href=3D"https://www.thinkreliability.com/root-cause-analysis-tool=
s/cause-mapping-template/"><em><span style=3D"background-color: white;">Cau=
se Mapping Investigation </span></em><span style=3D"background-color: white=
;">T</span><span style=3D"background-color: white;">emplate in Microsoft Ex=
cel</span></a> <span style=3D"color: black; background-color: white;">(whic=
h is free to download) was created to allow users to document, analyze and =
present their entire root cause analysis within one file using software you=
 probably already have on your computer. Each worksheet has a specific purp=
ose within the investigation and allows you to document the different parts=
 of a complete incident investigation. Instead of a 100+ page report, </spa=
n><a href=3D"https://blog.thinkreliability.com/cause-mapping-investigation-=
template-explained"><span style=3D"background-color: white;">this one file<=
/span></a><span style=3D"color: black; background-color: white;"> allows yo=
u to capture a basic, mid and detailed level analysis, along with all the e=
vidence, photos, diagrams and drawings. Different policies and procedures, =
PDFs and PowerPoint slides can be housed within one file. </span><a href=3D=
"https://youtu.be/ONibcKyIGEQ"><span style=3D"background-color: white;">Cli=
ck here</span></a><span style=3D"color: black; background-color: white;"> t=
o see a video overview of recent updates to the template as well as how the=
 template can be used for your complete incident investigations.</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin-top: 15pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; paddin=
g-left: 0in;"><span style=3D"color: black;">The Notes worksheet is part of =
the information tools and resource section that support the </span><span st=
yle=3D"color: black;"><a href=3D"https://blog.thinkreliability.com/problem-=
solving-three-basic-steps">three basic problem-solving steps</a></span><spa=
n style=3D"color: black;">. It captures additional information that is impo=
rtant but doesn=E2=80=99t necessarily make sense to include on the other ta=
bs. For example, this worksheet can house incident reports, witness stateme=
nts, emails, relevant policies and procedures, as well as notes about infor=
mation you may uncover as the investigation progresses. Think of it as the =
location for any miscellaneous information you collect.</span></p>
<h3 style=3D"margin-top: 15pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; paddi=
ng-left: 0in; font-weight: normal;"><span style=3D"color: black;">Documenti=
ng, Organizing Evidence With Notes</span></h3>
<p style=3D"margin-top: 15pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; paddin=
g-left: 0in;"><span style=3D"color: black;">Depending on the magnitude or s=
everity of your investigation, you may have a lot of evidence to be stored =
here. If the worksheet becomes difficult to manage, organize or use effecti=
vely, you may need to separate out the information by topic or type of evid=
ence. You can do so by </span><span style=3D"color: black;"><a href=3D"http=
s://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DWhBxyt4kAOk">copying the worksheet</a></span>=
<span style=3D"color: black;"> and renaming it to indicate what=E2=80=99s i=
ncluded. For example, you may decide to have a tab dedicated to witness sta=
tements or for the incident report. Using Microsoft Excel for your document=
ation allows you to adjust and customize the template to meet your organiza=
tion=E2=80=99s specific needs.</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin-top: 15pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; paddin=
g-left: 0in;"><span style=3D"color: black;">To learn more about how to use =
the <em>Cause Mapping </em>Incident Template in Microsoft Excel, </span><sp=
an style=3D"color: black;">join our </span><span style=3D"color: black;"><a=
 href=3D"https://www.thinkreliability.com/event/excel-tips-tricks-for-using=
-the-cause-mapping-template-7/">free 45-minute webinar =E2=80=9CExcel Tips =
&amp; Tricks for Using the Cause Mapping Template=E2=80=9D this Friday, Feb=
ruary 26</a></span><span style=3D"color: black;">.&nbsp;Don't worry if you =
can=E2=80=99t make it, register ahead of time, and we'll be sure to send yo=
u the recording after its conclusion.</span></p>
<p style=3D"margin-top: 15pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; paddin=
g-left: 0in;"><span style=3D"color: black;">For more in-depth instruction o=
n using the <em>Cause Mapping</em> method on your incident investigations, =
register for one of our upcoming online short courses focused on mastering =
your skills in Microsoft Excel, including </span><span style=3D"color: blac=
k;"><a href=3D"https://www.thinkreliability.com/event/how-to-document-cause=
-mapping-rca-investigations-online-short-course-2/">=E2=80=9CHow to Documen=
t Cause Mapping RCA Investigations=E2=80=9D this Thursday</a></span><span s=
tyle=3D"color: black;">, or one of our other investigation topics. See the =
full schedule of upcoming short courses&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color: b=
lack;"><a href=3D"https://www.thinkreliability.com/rca-training/online-shor=
t-course/">here</a></span><span style=3D"color: black;">.</span></p>
